  "response": "Here are some tips for making friends as an introvert in your CA IPCC coaching:\n\n1. Start small\n- Sit near friendly-looking people\n- Smile and be approachable\n- Make small talk during breaks\n\n2. Find common ground\n- Discuss study materials\n- Ask about exam preparation\n- Share notes or study tips\n\n3. Group study strategies\n- Join study groups\n- Participate in group discussions\n- Offer help with difficult topics\n\n4. Conversation starters\n- Ask about their background\n- Discuss coaching experiences\n- Talk about CA exam preparation challenges\n\n5. Be yourself\n- Don't try to be overly extroverted\n- Focus on genuine connections\n- Quality over quantity in friendships\n\n6. Use structured interactions\n- Participate in class activities\n- Join coaching-organized events\n- Attend extra classes or workshops\n\n7. Online connections\n- Connect on social media/WhatsApp groups\n- Share study resources\n- Interact digitally if face-to-face feels overwhelming\n\n8. Practice self-confidence\n- Believe in your abilities\n- Don't be afraid to initiate conversations\n- Remember everyone is also seeking connections\n\n9. Be patient with yourself\n- Building friendships takes time\n- Don't pressure yourself\n- Allow relationships to develop naturally",
